The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, June 23: Bengal will have evening courts if lawyers agree to the proposal. The state bar council will meet on July 3 to discuss the plan. The move could speed up nearly 20 lakh cases. The Centre has sanctioned Rs 109 crore for infrastructure for the courts.        
	Midnapore: Five susp- ected Maoists and an arms dealer have been arrested from Salboni and Belpahari in West Midnapore.         
	Calcutta: Expelled CPM leader Somnath Chatterjee will deliver the Jyoti Basu memorial lecture in the Assembly on July 8, the late CPM leaders birth anniversary.
                                                                                                                                                      
